The paper deals with constraint satisfaction problems and presents improved parameterized algorithms for solving them. This makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) the most likely categories, as they are directly related to algorithmic problem-solving. The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The mention of "linear bikernels" suggests a connection to computational geometry, making cs.CG (Computational Geometry) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the "above average" parameterization, which is a topic in parameterized complexity theory, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category as well.
